      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/result/synthesis-prior-hemolysis-studies",
      "type": "uofa:EvidenceItem",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior CFD hemolysis studies — power-law coefficient meta-analysis",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of twelve prior experimental and computational hemolysis studies published between 2005 and 2021. The synthesis consolidates power-law hemolysis model coefficients (C, alpha, beta) from Giersiepen-Wurzinger, Arora, and Zhang formulations across multiple pump geometries and operating conditions. Statistical meta-analysis yields pooled coefficient distributions used as Monte Carlo input priors. The synthesis also reviews shear exposure pathway assumptions and erythrocyte fragility data from five independent laboratories, providing the epistemic foundation for model input uncertainty characterisation in the present COU."
